01/09/2009
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Foreign Minister Cristian Diaconescu announced on Monday (August 31st) that coalition partners -- the Liberal Democratic Party and the Social Democratic Party -- have agreed to support former Agriculture Minister Dacian Ciolos, in becoming commissioner of agriculture in the next European Commission.
Diaconescu confirmed that he had received a green light from his colleagues to negotiate a portfolio for Romania.
He also mentioned that Romania has received positive signals that the agriculture position is available.
Commissioners are nominated by their respective governments and approved by the European Parliament.
(Ziua, Evenimentul Zilei, EurActiv, Nine o'clock - 01/09/09;
AFP - 31/08/09)
